* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* BZX84C8V2  -  8.2 V, 250 mW voltage-regulator (zener) diode, SOT-23
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Datasheet-DERIVED model (not a vendor .lib file -- Nexperia does not publish a
* downloadable SPICE model for this part; the automated vendor download
* endpoints block scripted access).  Parameters are fitted to the published
* characteristics so the reverse (breakdown) curve matches the datasheet,
* which is exactly what issue #3 needs to be trusted.
*
* Source: Nexperia "BZX84 series - Voltage regulator diodes", Product data
*         sheet Rev. 7, 1 January 2023.  Table 8, row BZX84-C8V2:
*         https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/data-sheet/BZX84_SER.pdf
*
* Datasheet points used for the fit (Tj = 25 C):
*   Vz          = 7.70 .. 8.70 V   (nominal 8.2 V) at Iz = 5 mA (test current)
*   rdif (max)  = 15 ohm  at Iz = 5 mA
*   rdif (max)  = 80 ohm  at Iz = 1 mA        <- the soft knee
*   IR          = 0.7 uA  at VR = 5 V
*   Cd          = 150 pF  at VR = 0 V, f = 1 MHz
*   Ptot        = 250 mW,  VF <= 0.9 V at IF = 10 mA
*
* Fit rationale:
*   In the ngspice breakdown region  I = -IBV*exp(-(BV+V)/(NBV*Vt))  the dynamic
*   resistance is  rdif ~= RS + NBV*Vt/Iz.  NBV=2.9, RS=0.5 gives
*       rdif(5 mA) ~= 15.5 ohm   and   rdif(1 mA) ~= 75 ohm   (both <= max),
*   and reproduces the soft knee: rdif(190 uA) ~= 410 ohm, so Vz sags to
*       Vz(190 uA) ~= 8.2 + NBV*Vt*ln(0.19/5) ~= 7.95 V.
*   Calibrating IBV at the 5 mA datasheet test current pins Vz = BV = 8.2 V
*   there, so the whole curve is anchored to the datasheet test condition.
*   This is the point of issue #3: a generic D(BV=8.2) calibrated at 5 mA with
*   the default sharp knee would read Vz ~= 8.2 V at 190 uA and be wrong.
*
* SANITY CHECK the run: op-point I(D1) should be ~190 uA and V(VREF) ~7.9-8.0 V.
* If you obtain the official vendor .lib later, drop it in and re-run; the deck
* only references the model name "BZX84C8V2".
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.model BZX84C8V2 D(
+ IS=1e-14 N=1 RS=0.5 CJO=150p VJ=0.75 M=0.33 TT=1n
+ BV=8.2 IBV=5m NBV=2.9 )
